Subject: [PATCH] ppu/include: cell-SDK-name lv2 sync compat shims

Tier-2 cell-SDK-source compat scaffolding.  reference cell SDK samples
that include <sys/synchronization.h> + <sys/ppu_thread.h> +
<sys/time_util.h> need PSL1GHT-side counterparts under those exact
paths so source compiles unmodified.  PSL1GHT exposes the same lv2
syscall surface but under different identifiers (sysCondCreate,
sysThreadCreate, etc.) — these new headers bridge the names without
duplicating the syscall machinery.

Five small new headers:

  cell/error.h               CELL_OK + CELL_ERROR_CAST.
  sys/return_code.h          cell-SDK-name forwarder to <cell/error.h>.
  sys/synchronization.h      sys_event_flag_* lv2syscall wrappers
                             (numbers verified against the reference cell SDK's
                             sys/syscall.h: 82/83/85/86/87/118/132/139)
                             plus SYS_EVENT_FLAG_WAIT_* constants and
                             the 32-byte sys_event_flag_attribute_t
                             matching the reference cell SDK exactly
                             (attr_protocol, attr_pshared, key, flags,
                             type, name[8]).  The
                             sys_event_flag_attribute_initialize macro
                             defaults to SYS_SYNC_PRIORITY +
                             SYS_SYNC_NOT_PROCESS_SHARED +
                             SYS_SYNC_WAITER_MULTIPLE per the cell SDK's macro.
                             Mutex/cond/sem/lwmutex cell-SDK-name wrappers
                             can be added as the next sample needs them.
  sys/ppu_thread.h           Inline forwarders from sys_ppu_thread_*
                             to PSL1GHT's sysThread* (cast args; same
                             ABI on PPC64).  Defines
                             SYS_PPU_THREAD_CREATE_JOINABLE etc.
  sys/time_util.h            SYS_TIMEBASE_GET macro reading PowerPC
                             TBU/TBL with the standard rollover loop.

samples/hello-ppu-event-flag/ ports the PPU half of the cell SDK's
samples/sdk/lv2/event_flag/event_flag.ppu.c (master + 5 worker
threads coordinating via two event flags).  SPU half stripped to
keep scope contained — the PPU-PPU master/worker scenario alone
exercises every syscall in the new <sys/synchronization.h>.
__cntlzd → __builtin_clzll (GCC builtin, same insn).

This unlocks the broader lv2-sample category for direct port without
further per-sample header work — the next event_flag-using or
threaded sample can `make` immediately.

diff --git a/ppu/include/cell/error.h b/ppu/include/cell/error.h
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..0000000
--- /dev/null
+++ b/ppu/include/cell/error.h
@@ -0,0 +1,24 @@
+/*! \file cell/error.h
+ \brief cell-SDK-source-compat shared error/return-code primitives.
+
+  Tiny header used by reference cell-SDK samples and most cell headers.
+  CELL_OK is the canonical "no error" value (always 0); CELL_ERROR_CAST
+  forces a constant to int when used inside #define CELL_X_ERROR_Y forms
+  to keep the type stable in GCC under -Wsign-compare.
+*/
+
+#ifndef __PSL1GHT_CELL_ERROR_H__
+#define __PSL1GHT_CELL_ERROR_H__
+
+#ifdef __cplusplus
+extern "C" {
+#endif
+
+#define CELL_OK                0
+#define CELL_ERROR_CAST(x)     ((int)(x))
+
+#ifdef __cplusplus
+}
+#endif
+
+#endif /* __PSL1GHT_CELL_ERROR_H__ */

diff --git a/ppu/include/sys/return_code.h b/ppu/include/sys/return_code.h
